definitions.definition: To express feelings of pain , dissatisfaction , or resentment .
examples: Joe was always complaining about the noise made by his neighbours.

definitions.definition: To make a formal accusation or bring a formal charge .
examples: They've complained about me to the police again.

definitions.definition: To creak or squeak , as a timber or wheel.

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To express feelings of pain , dissatisfaction , or resentment .
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) To make a formal accusation or bring a formal charge .
